page.title: 20Housing at Sutton-at-Hone
page.content:
This area is completely separate from Swanley,most of the building was done in the 1930s and 1950s.There were more flats and maisonettes than in the other areas we surveyed.The houses are very mixed,from the small Victorian terrace to the large modern houses and bungalows. 1 house had a moat all around it and was very big.The little terrace houses had gardens and there were some shops built in 1930.
This work has been done by the top Infants and Junior children at Birchwood C.P. School Swanley.
